This paper deals with the problem of optimizing the value of information, which is a key topic in machine learning and decision making. The proposed framework involves online learning and dynamic hypothesis enumeration, which are common techniques in the fields of machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of posterior sampling and establishes a bound on expected regret, which are topics in statistics and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the real-world application of interactive troubleshooting suggests a connection to systems and control theory (cs.SY) and data structures (cs.DS).
